spec: struct_extra51
version: ">=3.9"
backend: python_module(struct)

docs: https://docs.python.org/3/library/struct.html

provenance:
  derived_from:
    - "https://docs.python.org/3/library/struct.html — Python struct module documentation"
    - "Test vectors verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10"
  not_derived_from:
    - "CPython source: Modules/_struct.c"
    - "struct_extra50.zspec.zsdl — covers unpack/calcsize/pack_into/unpack_from/iter_unpack __class__.__module__.__eq__('builtins'); Struct/error __init__.__class__.__name__/__module__.__eq__('wrapper_descriptor'/'builtins')."
    - "struct_extra49.zspec.zsdl — covers struct module __dict__/__class__/__name__/__qualname__/__module__.__eq__('mappingproxy'/'builtins')."
    - "struct_extra48.zspec.zsdl — covers Struct/error __dict__/__class__/__name__/__qualname__/__module__.__eq__('mappingproxy'/'builtins')."
    - "struct_extra43.zspec.zsdl — covers Struct/pack/error __class__.__module__.__eq__('builtins') as three representative rows."
    - "struct_extra40.zspec.zsdl — covers Struct.__init__/__repr__ __name__.__eq__('__init__'/'__repr__') and __name__.__len__()==8."
    - "struct_extra21.zspec.zsdl — covers Struct.__init__/__repr__ __qualname__.__eq__ and __qualname__.__len__()."
  notes:
    - "This spec extends struct through struct_extra50; it does NOT duplicate invariants present in those files."
    - "Wave 222 theme: __repr__.__class__.__name__ checks + __weakref__ descriptor checks + __hash__ class name checks."
    - "Coverage gap 1: No prior struct spec checks __repr__.__class__.__name__ for Struct or error. struct_extra40 covers Struct.__repr__.__name__.__eq__('__repr__') (the bare name attribute of the descriptor itself) and Struct.__repr__.__name__.__len__()==8. struct_extra21 covers Struct.__repr__.__qualname__.__eq__('Struct.__repr__'). Neither checks the TYPE of the descriptor: Struct.__repr__.__class__.__name__. Struct is a C extension type; its __repr__ is a wrapper_descriptor (C slot wrapper for tp_repr). struct.error is an exception subclass (ultimately of BaseException, a C type); its __repr__ is also a wrapper_descriptor inherited from the C exception hierarchy. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "struct.Struct.__repr__.__class__.__name__ == 'wrapper_descriptor'. Struct is a C extension type; its __repr__ slot is exposed as a wrapper_descriptor. struct_extra40 covers __repr__.__name__.__eq__ and struct_extra21 covers __repr__.__qualname__.__eq__, but neither checks __repr__.__class__.__name__. No prior struct spec checks Struct.__repr__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('wrapper_descriptor'). Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "struct.error.__repr__.__class__.__name__ == 'wrapper_descriptor'. error is a Python-level exception class ultimately inheriting from BaseException (a C type); its __repr__ is a wrapper_descriptor inherited from the C exception type chain. No prior struct spec checks error.__repr__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('wrapper_descriptor'). Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "Coverage gap 2: No prior struct spec checks __hash__.__class__.__name__ for Struct or error. struct.Struct does not define __eq__, so it inherits __hash__ from object as a wrapper_descriptor. struct.error inherits __hash__ from the exception hierarchy (ultimately object); the TYPE-level __hash__ is a wrapper_descriptor. Struct instances are hashable (hash() succeeds). No prior spec checks Struct.__hash__.__class__.__name__ or error.__hash__.__class__.__name__. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "struct.Struct.__hash__.__class__.__name__ == 'wrapper_descriptor'. Struct does not define __eq__ or __hash__; __hash__ is inherited from object as a C slot wrapper (wrapper_descriptor). Struct instances are hashable. No prior struct spec checks Struct.__hash__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('wrapper_descriptor'). Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "struct.error.__hash__.__class__.__name__ == 'wrapper_descriptor'. error inherits __hash__ from the exception hierarchy (object); the TYPE-level __hash__ is a wrapper_descriptor. No prior struct spec checks error.__hash__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('wrapper_descriptor'). Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "Coverage gap 3: No prior struct spec checks __repr__.__class__.__name__ for pack, unpack, or calcsize. struct.pack/unpack/calcsize are builtin_function_or_method objects; their __repr__ is a method-wrapper (a bound wrapper around the __repr__ slot of the builtin_function_or_method type). This is distinct from the TYPE-level wrapper_descriptor: at the instance level (calling __repr__ on a builtin_function_or_method object), the result is a method-wrapper. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "struct.pack.__repr__.__class__.__name__ == 'method-wrapper'. pack is a builtin_function_or_method; accessing __repr__ on it yields a bound method-wrapper (the C slot wrapper bound to the specific builtin function object). No prior struct spec checks pack.__repr__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('method-wrapper'). Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "struct.unpack.__repr__.__class__.__name__ == 'method-wrapper'. Same pattern as pack. No prior struct spec checks unpack.__repr__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('method-wrapper'). Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "struct.calcsize.__repr__.__class__.__name__ == 'method-wrapper'. Same pattern as pack/unpack. No prior struct spec checks calcsize.__repr__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('method-wrapper'). Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "All expected values verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
  created_at: "2026-04-10T00:00:00Z"

error_model: python_exceptions

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# struct.Struct and struct.error __repr__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('wrapper_descriptor')
#
# No prior struct spec checks __repr__.__class__.__name__ for Struct or error.
# struct_extra40 covers Struct.__repr__.__name__.__eq__('__repr__') — the bare
# name attribute of the descriptor — and struct_extra21 covers
# Struct.__repr__.__qualname__.__eq__. Neither checks Struct.__repr__.__class__
# (the TYPE of the descriptor itself). Struct and error are both C extension types
# (or inherit from C types); their __repr__ is exposed as a wrapper_descriptor.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

table struct_extra51.repr_class_name_eq:
  description: "struct.Struct/__repr__/__class__/__name__.__eq__('wrapper_descriptor') and error same — C extension types expose __repr__ as a wrapper_descriptor (C slot wrapper for tp_repr); struct_extra40 covers Struct.__repr__.__name__.__eq__ (bare name) and struct_extra21 covers __repr__.__qualname__.__eq__, but neither checks __repr__.__class__.__name__; no prior struct spec checks __repr__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('wrapper_descriptor') for Struct or error"
  kind: python_call_eq
  category: type_structure
  id_prefix: structr51

  columns: [id, function, args, expected]
  rows:
    - [Struct_repr_class_name_eq, Struct.__repr__.__class__.__name__.__eq__, ["wrapper_descriptor"], true]
    - [error_repr_class_name_eq,  error.__repr__.__class__.__name__.__eq__,  ["wrapper_descriptor"], true]

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# struct.Struct and struct.error TYPE-level __hash__.__class__.__name__
#
# No prior struct spec checks __hash__.__class__.__name__ for Struct or error.
# struct.Struct does not define __eq__ or __hash__, so it inherits __hash__
# from object as a wrapper_descriptor (C slot wrapper for tp_hash). Struct
# instances are hashable. struct.error similarly inherits __hash__ from the
# exception hierarchy (ultimately object). Both TYPE-level __hash__ attributes
# are wrapper_descriptor objects.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

table struct_extra51.hash_class_name_eq:
  description: "struct.Struct/__hash__/__class__/__name__.__eq__('wrapper_descriptor') and error same — C extension types inherit __hash__ from object as a slot wrapper; Struct does not define __eq__ so __hash__ inheritance is preserved; Struct instances are hashable; no prior struct spec checks __hash__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('wrapper_descriptor') for Struct or error"
  kind: python_call_eq
  category: type_structure
  id_prefix: structr51

  columns: [id, function, args, expected]
  rows:
    - [Struct_hash_class_name_eq, Struct.__hash__.__class__.__name__.__eq__, ["wrapper_descriptor"], true]
    - [error_hash_class_name_eq,  error.__hash__.__class__.__name__.__eq__,  ["wrapper_descriptor"], true]

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# struct.pack/unpack/calcsize __repr__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('method-wrapper')
#
# No prior struct spec checks __repr__.__class__.__name__ for pack, unpack, or
# calcsize. These are builtin_function_or_method objects (C functions in the
# _struct extension). When __repr__ is accessed on a builtin_function_or_method
# instance, the result is a 'method-wrapper' — the C slot wrapper bound to the
# specific builtin function object. This is distinct from the TYPE-level
# wrapper_descriptor: method-wrapper is the bound form, wrapper_descriptor is
# the unbound descriptor form.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

invariant struct_extra51.pack.repr_class_name_eq:
  description: "struct.pack.__repr__.__class__.__name__ == 'method-wrapper' — pack is a builtin_function_or_method; accessing __repr__ on an instance yields a bound method-wrapper; distinct from wrapper_descriptor (the TYPE-level slot descriptor); no prior struct spec checks pack.__repr__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('method-wrapper')"
  category: type_structure
  kind: python_call_eq
  function: pack.__repr__.__class__.__name__.__eq__
  args: ["method-wrapper"]
  expected: true

invariant struct_extra51.unpack.repr_class_name_eq:
  description: "struct.unpack.__repr__.__class__.__name__ == 'method-wrapper' — same bound method-wrapper pattern as pack; no prior struct spec checks unpack.__repr__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('method-wrapper')"
  category: type_structure
  kind: python_call_eq
  function: unpack.__repr__.__class__.__name__.__eq__
  args: ["method-wrapper"]
  expected: true

invariant struct_extra51.calcsize.repr_class_name_eq:
  description: "struct.calcsize.__repr__.__class__.__name__ == 'method-wrapper' — same bound method-wrapper pattern as pack/unpack; no prior struct spec checks calcsize.__repr__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('method-wrapper')"
  category: type_structure
  kind: python_call_eq
  function: calcsize.__repr__.__class__.__name__.__eq__
  args: ["method-wrapper"]
  expected: true
